02:51:16,240 --> 02:51:23,599
I've never carried a gun. Normally, my 
philosophy is that if a job involves using a gun,  

1532
02:51:24,240 --> 02:51:29,760
it's a job not worth taking. That's on 
account of the potential health risks.  

1533
02:51:30,720 --> 02:51:36,640
I knew if Joe had to use a gun, he'd be 
more accurate than I could ever hope to be.

1534
02:51:38,240 --> 02:51:45,840
There would be no weekend break. I 
wanted to bring this case to a close.
 
 

1535
02:51:48,160 --> 02:51:49,200
CHAPTER FOURTEEN

1536
02:51:50,160 --> 02:51:50,880
Memories

1537
02:51:53,040 --> 02:52:00,160
Saturday morning, the weather forecast promised 
clear, mild weather over the weekend. Perfect  

1538
02:52:00,160 --> 02:52:04,000
conditions for landing immigrants 
along the Long Island shore?  

1539
02:52:05,520 --> 02:52:13,041
Joe and I got an early start and had arrived at 
East 43rd Street by 8:00 AM. The light on the  

1540
02:52:13,040 --> 02:52:19,840
answering machine was flashing, a message from 
Mrs. Romanov asking me to call her urgently.

1541
02:52:21,120 --> 02:52:23,519
"Mrs. Romanov? Marley here."

1542
02:52:24,560 --> 02:52:32,241
"I'm so glad you've called. I've had some 
dreadful news." said Mrs. Romanov. "You  

1543
02:52:32,240 --> 02:52:38,960
remember the bartender at the Odessa Steps 
who witnessed Zernov leaving with De La Cruz?  

1544
02:52:40,000 --> 02:52:48,560
He's been badly beaten up. And not only him. 
The manager of the bar was also attacked."

1545
02:52:49,760 --> 02:52:51,760
"I'm terribly sorry to hear that.  

1546
02:52:52,560 --> 02:52:58,720
This is probably Zernov's work. He's 
making sure they stay silent," I said.

1547
02:52:59,920 --> 02:53:04,800
"Well, he's succeeded. 
They're absolutely terrified.  

1548
02:53:05,600 --> 02:53:10,480
I heard about this through contacts 
at the Immigrant Welfare Society.  

1549
02:53:11,359 --> 02:53:17,200
It was a brutal attack. That man 
Zernov must not get away with it."

1550
02:53:18,720 --> 02:53:22,960
I was just thinking about 
contacting Oldenberg and Lockhart  

1551
02:53:22,960 --> 02:53:28,240
when the phone rang. It was Stella, 
