parks, dominated by the huge roller coaster 
rides soon came into view. One of those rides  

1700
03:09:28,080 --> 03:09:33,760
which had terrified and delighted me as a 
child was still operating - the Cyclone.  

1701
03:09:34,800 --> 03:09:40,800
I still remember the way the train of little cars 
would climb up the track to the highest point,  

1702
03:09:41,520 --> 03:09:46,880
then dive and shake down what felt 
like a series of near-vertical drops.

1703
03:09:48,319 --> 03:09:55,359
There was another roller coaster ride standing 
behind locked gates. I examined the curves  

1704
03:09:55,359 --> 03:10:04,399
and slopes. Now I recognized it as the old 
Thunderbolt, another childhood favorite. Sadly,  

1705
03:10:04,399 --> 03:10:11,839
it was now in a state of total disrepair with 
peeling paintwork, rust, and fire damage.

1706
03:10:12,479 --> 03:10:19,040
The sun was now sinking low and the western 
sky was glowing with shades of orange and pink.  

1707
03:10:20,160 --> 03:10:22,160
It was going to be a long night.

1708
03:10:23,600 --> 03:10:30,000
It was completely dark when I received the 
first call from Oldenberg. The Coast Guard  

1709
03:10:30,000 --> 03:10:37,760
had been following the movements of ships off the 
Long Island coast all day. As the light faded,  

1710
03:10:37,760 --> 03:10:44,000
a fishing boat had turned towards the shore and 
was now heading in the direction of Fire Island.

1711
03:10:45,359 --> 03:10:53,839
"It looks like it's all happening, Joe," 
I said. "Time to get in position."
 
 

