boat land a party of ten men and four packages 
at the eastern end of Fire Island. A white Ford  

1719
03:11:37,439 --> 03:11:44,160
truck had arrived, driven by a tall, heavily 
built guy who matched Zernov's description.  

1720
03:11:45,279 --> 03:11:51,040
The truck had picked up the men and the packages 
and had been spotted leaving Fire Island.  

1721
03:11:52,720 --> 03:11:58,560
Later, Oldenberg informed us that the 
truck was now on Long Island Highway 27,  

1722
03:11:59,200 --> 03:12:06,239
heading toward Freeport. The NYPD helicopter 
was following its movements at a safe distance.

1723
03:12:07,760 --> 03:12:13,360
It was around eleven o'clock when we heard that 
the truck was approaching the Coney Island area.  

1724
03:12:14,160 --> 03:12:20,960
The helicopter pilot was having trouble following 
the vehicle. An ocean storm was brewing,  

1725
03:12:20,960 --> 03:12:27,200
and a lot of fog was rolling in. Not ideal 
conditions for surveillance from the air.

1726
03:12:28,560 --> 03:12:35,680
The pilot now reported that the truck was on the 
eastern side of JFK airport, on the Belt Parkway,  

1727
03:12:36,239 --> 03:12:42,559
which circles the coast around Jamaica 
Bay. Frequent banks of fog continued to  

1728
03:12:42,560 --> 03:12:49,440
make observation from the air a problem. Then 
we heard a panicky note in the pilot's voice.  

1729
03:12:50,479 --> 03:12:55,120
"Captain Oldenberg, we're losing 
him... No, there he is again..."

1730
03:12:55,840 --> 03:13:04,080
This is getting difficult. There's more fog 
ahead. Lost him. No, we've got him again. Captain,  

1731
03:13:04,080 --> 03:13:09,920
we may not be able to keep the suspect under 
surveillance. The truck's heading east on the  

1732
03:13:09,920 --> 03:13:17,440
Belt Parkway now. I suggest you move all units 
now to the Belt Parkway exits for Coney Island."

1733
03:13:18,880 --> 03:13:24,720
Finally we heard the pilot admit defeat. 
"Captain Oldenberg, we've lost him."

1734
03:13:25,920 --> 03:13:30,560
There was radio silence for a 
time. Then a sighting of the  

1735
03:13:30,560 --> 03:13:36,081
truck leaving the Belt Parkway at exit 
seven and heading towards Ocean Parkway.

1736
03:13:37,439 --> 03:13:43,839
A call from Oldenberg: "Marley, the 
truck's in Coney Island, on Ocean Parkway.  

1737
03:13:44,479 --> 03:13:50,959
I have one unit already following, and I'm 
ordering all units in. I'll keep you posted."

1738
03:13:52,000 --> 03:13:59,200
We continued listening in on the police radio. 
At first everything went smoothly until the  

1739
03:13:59,200 --> 03:14:04,800
intersection at Brighton Beach Parkway. 
An officer was speaking to Oldenberg:  

1740
03:14:05,840 --> 03:14:12,400
"Captain, we have the suspect in sight. 
We're about fifty yards behind. Red light,  

1741
03:14:12,399 --> 03:14:16,960
coming to a stop. Hey! He's run 
right through the red light."

1742
03:14:18,000 --> 03:14:20,399
"Try and follow," ordered Oldenberg.

1743
03:14:21,680 --> 03:14:26,000
Suddenly, over the radio, 
we heard the scream of tires  

1744
03:14:26,000 --> 03:14:32,080
followed by two impacts of steel 
against steel. Then silence.

1745
03:14:33,680 --> 03:14:36,000
"Captain Oldenberg," said the officer.  

1746
03:14:36,720 --> 03:14:42,960
"We just ran into the side of a cab, and our 
other car is buried in the back of our car.  

1747
03:14:43,920 --> 03:14:49,920
Nobody hurt, just shaken up. Sorry, 
but both cars are out of action."

1748
03:14:51,120 --> 03:14:56,720
"Where's the third car?" shouted 
Oldenberg. "Get after the suspect!"

1749
03:14:57,920 --> 03:15:02,000
"Sorry Captain. The traffic's now 
at a standstill at the intersection.  

1750
03:15:02,640 --> 03:15:07,600
Nothing's moving. The third car 
can't get through. We've lost him."

1751
03:15:08,399 --> 03:15:10,239
"Hell!" swore Oldenberg.

1752
03:15:11,600 --> 03:15:18,000
A moment later, Oldenberg called me on the 
cell phone. "Marley. I hate to admit this..."

1753
03:15:18,800 --> 03:15:22,320
"But you've lost the suspect," I finished for him.  

1754
03:15:23,279 --> 03:15:29,759
"We know, Oldenberg. We've been listening in 
on the police radio. Joe and I are going to  

1755
03:15:29,760 --> 03:15:36,080
cruise around the neighborhood, just in case 
we spot something. I suggest you do the same."

1756
03:15:37,600 --> 03:15:44,640
I asked Joe to head towards Surf Avenue. 
Soon we were passing by the amusement parks,  

1757
03:15:44,640 --> 03:15:50,000
with the ghostly shapes of the big wheels 
and roller coasters appearing out of the fog.

1758
03:15:51,520 --> 03:15:57,121
As we made our way along the avenue, I started 
thinking about the surveillance photographs  

1759
03:15:57,120 --> 03:16:05,040
of Zernov. Suddenly, every piece in the puzzle 
joined together to give me a complete picture.  

1760
03:16:06,160 --> 03:16:12,880
That photograph of Zernov outside a set 
of gates. I thought back to our tour of  

1761
03:16:12,880 --> 03:16:20,239
the sights of Coney Island. The old Thunderbolt 
roller coaster. The gates with the peeling paint.  

1762
03:16:21,439 --> 03:16:25,519
Boris Tchernov's statement that 
they were taken to some sort of  

1763
03:16:25,520 --> 03:16:32,560
factory building with a railroad track on 
the floor. I knew then where they had to be.

1764
03:16:33,920 --> 03:16:38,160
"Joe, the old Thunderbolt 
roller coaster. And step on it."

1765
03:16:39,600 --> 03:16:47,440
The car sped towards West 16th Street, off Surf 
Avenue. As we approached the roller coaster,  

1766
03:16:47,439 --> 03:16:51,519
the ruined structure gradually 
came into focus through the fog.  

1767
03:16:52,800 --> 03:17:00,960
I told Joe to kill the headlights as we neared the 
gates. All was quiet and the street was deserted.

1768
03:17:02,560 --> 03:17:08,800
Signs reading 'Dangerous structure - No 
admittance' were attached to the fence  

1769
03:17:08,800 --> 03:17:17,040
surrounding the old ride. The gates were at least 
ten feet high but with Joe's help I climbed over.  

1770
03:17:18,319 --> 03:17:25,840
On the other side, there was a lock and key with 
a thick steel chain. I tried the key in the lock.  

1771
03:17:26,800 --> 03:17:32,320
It turned without any effort. This 
entrance was obviously used regularly.  

1772
03:17:33,600 --> 03:17:35,920
I opened the gates to let Joe through.

1773
03:17:37,200 --> 03:17:43,359
We looked around us. Now, there was sufficient 
moonlight to provide better visibility.  

1774
03:17:44,720 --> 03:17:52,240
About seventy-five yards away, I spotted a 
white Ford truck and a limo parked alongside  

1775
03:17:52,239 --> 03:17:59,359
a one-story building in the shadows of the roller 
coaster structure. No lights could be seen.

1776
03:18:00,880 --> 03:18:08,640
A door opened. A sudden flash of light from 
the interior of the building, then darkness.

1777
03:18:10,000 --> 03:18:17,520
"Get down!" I whispered to Joe. We dived for 
cover behind an ancient roller coaster car.  

1778
03:18:18,800 --> 03:18:27,279
I looked over the edge and watched. It was Zernov. 
He started to walk in the direction of the gates,  

1779
03:18:27,279 --> 03:18:34,719
shining a flashlight from side to side. We kept 
our heads low as the ray of light was directed  

1780
03:18:34,720 --> 03:18:43,440
towards us. Then he went back inside. My mouth 
was dry and my heart was beating like a drum.

1781
03:18:44,640 --> 03:18:49,040
"Joe, we need back-up. Zernov's in there,  

1782
03:18:49,040 --> 03:18:53,920
and presumably Mossolov. There 
could be more of the gang inside."

1783
03:18:55,279 --> 03:19:03,279
I called Oldenberg and gave him our location. 
"When you arrive, I want you to park so your car's  

1784
03:19:03,279 --> 03:19:12,559
blocking the gate, OK? Same for the other police 
car. Then we'll have the exit sealed. But hurry!"

1785
03:19:13,920 --> 03:19:18,000
Oldenberg made rapid time. Two minutes later we  

1786
03:19:18,000 --> 03:19:24,160
heard the deep hum of the engine. Oldenberg 
and his sergeant slipped inside the gates.

1787
03:19:25,279 --> 03:19:31,840
"Over here," I whispered to Oldenberg. 
"Where's the other car?" I demanded.  

1788
03:19:32,640 --> 03:19:39,520
Oldenberg spoke urgently into his cell phone. His 
officers had gone to the wrong roller coaster.

1789
03:19:40,800 --> 03:19:48,320
Oldenberg considered the situation for a moment, 
then announced: "We're going in. All the evidence  

1790
03:19:48,319 --> 03:19:55,439
should be there. Any delay could mean we 
lose the key players. You with me, Marley?"

1791
03:19:56,399 --> 03:19:57,920
"All the way, Oldenberg."

1792
03:19:59,520 --> 03:20:06,960
We hurried over to the door of the building. From 
inside, we could hear conversation in Russian,  

1793
03:20:06,960 --> 03:20:13,840
and laughter. Although there were only the 
four of us, we had the element of surprise.

1794
03:20:14,479 --> 03:20:18,479
Oldenberg, the sergeant, and 
Joe had their weapons ready.  

1795
03:20:19,439 --> 03:20:25,839
Oldenberg nodded to his sergeant, who 
kicked the door wide open. We rushed inside.  

1796
03:20:26,640 --> 03:20:30,880
The sergeant shouted: "Police! 
Don't move! Hands in the air!"

1797
03:20:32,239 --> 03:20:39,760
For a second, the scene before us seemed to be 
frozen in time. The building was lit by oil lamps.  

1798
03:20:40,720 --> 03:20:46,960
Ten young men were sitting on benches around a 
table, drinking coffee and eating sandwiches.  

1799
03:20:48,080 --> 03:20:55,040
Zernov, who was sitting at another table, 
stared at us in disbelief. The big man from  

1800
03:20:55,040 --> 03:21:02,479
the photographs was there sitting next to Zernov. 
The woman with long dark hair was standing behind  

1801
03:21:02,479 --> 03:21:09,839
them. On the floor was the railroad track 
which Tchernov had mentioned. In a corner  

1802
03:21:09,840 --> 03:21:16,080
lay an old roller coaster car, on its side. 
The place must have been the repair workshop.

1803
03:21:17,600 --> 03:21:20,400
The woman didn't seem to be alarmed at all.  

1804
03:21:21,439 --> 03:21:27,120
Zernov looked towards her, with a confused 
expression, as if expecting instructions.  

1805
03:21:28,479 --> 03:21:33,679
Then she turned towards Zernov and screamed: 
"Don't just stand there. Do something!"

1806
03:21:35,040 --> 03:21:41,840
He suddenly got up and reached for his gun, 
but before he could aim it, two shots rang out.  

1807
03:21:42,960 --> 03:21:48,720
He spun around with the impact of the 
bullets. Then he crashed to the floor,  

1808
03:21:49,359 --> 03:21:55,759
firing his gun wildly. A bullet 
passed through one of the oil lamps,  

1809
03:21:55,760 --> 03:22:00,480
smashing the glass. A cloud 
of gunsmoke hung in the air.

1810
03:22:01,920 --> 03:22:09,840
The place now seemed unnaturally quiet. For 
a second everyone stood motionless. Then we  

1811
03:22:09,840 --> 03:22:18,160
rushed forward. There were two bullet holes in 
Zernov's chest. Blood was dripping from his mouth  

1812
03:22:18,160 --> 03:22:26,160
and he was gasping for breath. He didn't 
look as if he had long to live. Meanwhile,  

1813
03:22:26,160 --> 03:22:32,399
the woman had thrown herself to the ground 
and had landed in a pool of rust-colored, oily  

1814
03:22:32,399 --> 03:22:39,599
water. As she raised herself, her face and hair 
and were dripping with the orange-black liquid.

1815
03:22:41,120 --> 03:22:45,920
I looked at the guy still sitting 
at the table. "Are you Mossolov?"

1816
03:22:47,040 --> 03:22:55,760
He stared at me, almost paralyzed with fear. "I'm 
just the driver," he stammered. "Don't shoot me."

1817
03:22:57,040 --> 03:23:00,000
The woman was now wiping the oil from her face.  

1818
03:23:00,800 --> 03:23:05,440
She looked down at her feet, not 
making eye contact with anybody.

1819
03:23:06,560 --> 03:23:14,000
Then, a slight movement from Zernov. With 
a painful effort, he slowly pointed a  

1820
03:23:14,000 --> 03:23:23,840
bloody finger towards the woman. Then the gasping 
stopped. His eyes open wide in a lifeless stare.

1821
03:23:25,520 --> 03:23:33,360
We looked at the woman in astonishment. Was 
she Mossolov? She remained standing there,  

1822
03:23:33,359 --> 03:23:38,799
looking down at the floor. The woman's 
handbag was lying on the table.  

1823
03:23:39,680 --> 03:23:45,120
I quickly found a driver's 
license: Katarina Mossolov.  

1824
03:23:46,479 --> 03:23:53,599
I showed the document to Oldenberg. "Let 
me introduce you to Mossolov," I said.

1825
03:23:54,800 --> 03:23:58,560
"Well, would you believe it!" exclaimed Oldenberg.

1826
03:24:00,080 --> 03:24:07,279
Everybody's attention was focused on Mossolov. But 
suddenly there was the sound of rapid footsteps.  

1827
03:24:08,080 --> 03:24:13,680
"Hey, where's the driver?" asked 
the sergeant urgently. From outside,  

1828
03:24:13,680 --> 03:24:21,280
we heard the sound of a motor. Then tires spinning 
and screaming as the limo raced to the gates.

1829
03:24:22,720 --> 03:24:25,840
"He won't get far," remarked Oldenberg.

1830
03:24:27,040 --> 03:24:34,960
Then came the crash of breaking wood and bending 
metal. Footsteps running down the street. A shout:  

1831
03:24:35,520 --> 03:24:40,960
"Police! Stop right there!" The 
other police car had finally arrived.

1832
03:24:42,080 --> 03:24:46,960
"They've got him," said Oldenberg. 
"From the sound of the crash,  

1833
03:24:46,960 --> 03:24:54,720
that's another NYPD car out of action. Still, 
cars are replaceable, good officers aren't."

1834
03:24:56,160 --> 03:24:58,639
I had one last favor to ask Oldenberg.  

1835
03:24:59,680 --> 03:25:05,040
"Before you charge Mossolov, I want 
a word with her. Just trust me, OK?"

1836
03:25:06,479 --> 03:25:11,040
She looked at me blankly. Oily liquid 
was still dripping from her hair.

1837
03:25:12,239 --> 03:25:20,479
"I don't enjoy being threatened," I said to her 
coldly. "The last time I met your man Zernov,  

1838
03:25:20,479 --> 03:25:28,319
he promised to break my legs if I 
didn't behave. Now look at him. The NYPD  

1839
03:25:28,319 --> 03:25:36,080
already has enough evidence against you to put 
you away for a very long time. The only choice  

1840
03:25:36,080 --> 03:25:42,880
you have is to cooperate. Unless you'd like 
my muscle man Joe to help persuade you."

1841
03:25:44,399 --> 03:25:50,000
I must have sounded convincing. I knew 
it was an empty threat, but she believed  

1842
03:25:50,000 --> 03:25:57,600
me. She looked around in alarm. Joe grinned 
unpleasantly at her to back up the message.

1843
03:25:58,960 --> 03:26:03,840
"So tell me. Did you have 
Romanov murdered?" I asked.

1844
03:26:04,560 --> 03:26:11,040
"All right. I admit it. I ordered 
Romanov's death," she said in a low,  

1845
03:26:11,040 --> 03:26:17,840
tired voice. "He knew too much and had been 
asking too many questions about my operation.  

1846
03:26:19,040 --> 03:26:26,640
Nick was carrying out my orders. But the fool 
made everything too complicated. I told him to  

1847
03:26:26,640 --> 03:26:35,201
make it look like a simple car-jacking. Nothing 
fancy. Then he found that stupid drunk in the  

1848
03:26:35,200 --> 03:26:43,760
Odessa Steps. I don't know who was more stupid, 
Nick or the drunk. Not that it matters any more."

1849
03:26:45,120 --> 03:26:53,279
I had the confession I wanted. Case closed. 
"Oldenberg, did you catch all that?" I asked.

1850
03:26:54,000 --> 03:27:00,560
"Everything, Marley. And I didn't hear you 
making any threats. May I congratulate you."

1851
03:27:01,840 --> 03:27:04,880
That was a compliment indeed, 
coming from the captain.

1852
03:27:06,000 --> 03:27:12,399
"Thanks. She's all yours now. Will you 
arrange the immediate release of De La Cruz?  

1853
03:27:13,359 --> 03:27:18,399
He'll need a statement to the effect that 
he was wrongfully arrested and charged,  

1854
03:27:18,399 --> 03:27:21,920
and of course an official apology from the NYPD.  

1855
03:27:23,040 --> 03:27:27,840
His lawyer will also be asking for 
financial compensation for wrongful arrest."

1856
03:27:28,960 --> 03:27:31,040
"You got it," replied Oldenberg.

1857
03:27:32,560 --> 03:27:39,360
My hands started to tremble violently. I 
knew that old familiar reaction to shock.  

1858
03:27:40,319 --> 03:27:47,599
I felt a wave of exhaustion going through my body. 
But there were still two more things I had to do;  

1859
03:27:48,720 --> 03:27:51,360
first a call to Mrs. Romanov.

1860
03:27:52,560 --> 03:27:55,840
"Mrs. Romanov? I know who murdered your husband.  

1861
03:27:56,880 --> 03:28:04,000
Nick Zernov acting under the orders of a 
Katarina Mossolov, the woman behind the immigrant  

1862
03:28:04,000 --> 03:28:12,399
smuggling. Zernov is now dead and Mossolov is 
under arrest. You'll get a full report on Monday."

1863
03:28:13,680 --> 03:28:19,120
"Thank God you're safe," said Mrs. 
Romanov. "I can't thank you enough."

1864
03:28:20,720 --> 03:28:23,840
And a call to Stella. "It's Nat.  

1865
03:28:24,479 --> 03:28:30,639
We have all the proof. Jose's going to 
be a free man. We've cleared his name."

1866
03:28:32,000 --> 03:28:39,279
"Oh, Nat, I'm so relieved. I don't 
know what to say. It's like huge  

1867
03:28:39,279 --> 03:28:45,040
weight's been lifted from me. I'll have to 
phone around to all the family right now."

1868
03:28:46,160 --> 03:28:49,599
"You do that, Stella. I'll see you on Monday."

1869
03:28:51,200 --> 03:28:54,080
I took one last look around the repair shop.  

1870
03:28:55,040 --> 03:29:02,560
The glow of the oil lamps, Zernov lifeless on 
the floor, dead eyes staring into empty space,  

1871
03:29:03,760 --> 03:29:08,560
Mossolov now in handcuffs, with an 
expression of complete disbelief.  

1872
03:29:10,080 --> 03:29:15,600
The illegal immigrants were still sitting at 
the table, looking around in shocked silence.  

1873
03:29:16,960 --> 03:29:21,920
What an introduction to the 
U.S.A., the land of opportunity!  

1874
03:29:23,279 --> 03:29:29,679
Time to get back to some of that predictable, 
routine work like divorce, bad debts,  

1875
03:29:29,680 --> 03:29:37,520
and missing persons. It was safe and dull, paid 
the bills, and didn't involve being shot at.

1876
03:29:38,880 --> 03:29:47,840
"Come on, Joe. That's quite enough excitement 
for one night. Let's go home."
 
 
 
 

1877
03:30:09,399 --> 03:30:10,399
-  

1878
03:30:10,399 --> 03:30:10,746
THE END -

